Here is a design for this:<br>
<br>
1. Take two holllow 5 kilogram hemispheres of pure<br>
Pu 239. Place a a small  hollow sphere of berylium <br>
metal in their center. Then wield them inside two 1 inch <br>
thick  hemispheres of natural uranium metal.Then wield<br>
 these hemisphere assemblys to make a solid spherical<br>
metal core,with the small hollow sphere of berylium inside it.<br>
 There is a vacume inside the hollow sphere of berylium.<br>
<br>
2.  Then make a a .25 inch thick hollow sphere of steel. The <br>
diameter of the hollow steel sphere can be 60 inches, 36 inches, or 24 inches. There are 4 steel bars attached to this sphere which are screwed into a cylindrical or perhaps light bulb shaped  outer casing of steel. These are the mounts for placing the core inside of the casing of the device. There is a bolt on nose cone, and and some bolt on  maitainence panels <br>
on the outer casing.<br>
<br>
3. Then cut a 10 inch diameter hole in the top of this<br>
hollow steel sphere. Then make a steel cap that can be bolted onto this hole to close it. There is a needle hole<br>
in the cap with a  a steel screw in plug to seal it.<br>
<br>
4.Then inject 300  kilograms of liquid tnt through the the<br>
cap  hole until the hollow sphere is half full. Then press the atimic core into the exact center of  this steel sphere and let the tnt harden around it. Then inject 300 more kilograms of tnt until the hollow steel sphere is full of tnt. Screw on the cap and and screw in the plug into the plug hole. Then let the tnt harden and set into a hollow sphere of tnt around the core.<br>
<br>
5.Then place exactly 32 symmetrical detonators on the hollow steel sphere. Connect them with either electric wires or ammonium nitrate detonating cords in 4 series circuits of eight.  Connect them to a radio remote controled solenoid <br>
 switch.<br>
<br>
6. The 4 firing circuits of eight detonators are exploded<br>
to detonate the hollow sphere of tnt around the core,<br>
when you are ready to create a 20 kiloton to perhaps an<br>
 80 kiloton atomic explosion. <br>
<br>
 7. Then the atomic core is compressed, and collapsed to fill the vacume cavity inside the hollow berylium sphere at the center.This makes  the core more, dense and more compact. This will create at least a 2 fold compression (density increase) making the core = to 4 critical masses. This will result in an atomic explosion immediately.<br>
